<!-- Help Templates -->

<script type="text/template" id="customize-assignment-help-template">
<h4>Student Overrides</h4>
<p>The students listed are only those that are assigned to this set.  To change an individual date/time, click on 
the desired date and change it.  To make changes to two or more students:
<ul><li> select the checkboxes of the students</li>
<li> change the date/time at the bottom of the screen </li>
<li> click "Save Changes".  </li>
</ul>

You can filter down the results by typing in the "search" box.  
The results will be dispayed below.  To search for section 2 type "section:2" or type "recitation:3" to find all students in recitation 3.</p>
</script>


<script type="text/template" id="problem-set-details-help-template">
<h4>Problem Set Properties</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>The basic properties (open, due and answer dates) as well as visibility and reduced scoring.</li>
    <li>To change any of the dates, click on the date and select (or type) in a new one.</li>
    <li>To change the time of the open, due or answer dates, click on the clock and type in a new time.</li>
    <li>One can easily assign this set to all users, but the "Assign to All Users" button.
  </ul>
</script>

<script type="text/template" id="problem-set-assign-users-help-template">
<p>The list on the left is those users assigned to this set.  The list on the right are those that are not.</p>
<p>To assign specific users:
<ol>
<li>Select the users on the "unassigned" (right) list</li>
<li>Click the "Assign" button</li>
<li>Those students will now move from the unassigned to assigned list.</li>
</ol>
</p>
<p>To unassign specific users:
<ol>
<li>Select the users on the "assigned" (left) list</li>
<li>Click the "UnAssign" button</li>
<li>Those students will now move from the assigned to unassigned list.</li>
</ol>
</p>

</script>

<script type="text/template" id="problem-set-view-help-template">
<h4>Problems</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>The problems will load dynamically.  You can view the tags on all problems with the "View Tags" button.</li>
    <li>To reorder problems, click the <button class="btn btn-default btn-sm"><i class="fa fa-arrows-v"></i></button> and drag to a new position in the list. </li>
    <li>To remove a problem, click the <button class="btn btn-default btn-sm"><i class="fa fa-trash-o"></i></button> button. You can undo the delete by clicking the "Undo Delete button". </li>
    <li>To view a problem with a new random seed, click the <button class="btn btn-default btn-sm"><i class="fa fa-refresh"></i></button> button.</li>
    <li>To change the value (or weight) of a problem, type in a new value and it will be updated automatically.</li>
  </ul>
</script>


